perfSONAR_PS::Collectors::Daemon README File
==========================================

Description
-----------

The perfSONAR_PS::Collectors::Daemon is the main daemon that is used to start
perfSONAR collectors. To use the daemon, install the modules for the collectors
one is interested in and configure the services in collector.conf.

Installation
------------

 CPAN installation
 -----------------

    perl -MCPAN -e 'install perfSONAR_PS::Collectors::Daemon'

 Standard installation
 ---------------------

    Prerequisites:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

Configuration
-------------

Once installed, run the program "psConfigureCollectors". This program will ask
a series of questions allowing you to specify which collectors to enable and
how each collector is configured.


